From 63a34e22d58324ece84ce7b9240d8180d05bc8d8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 20:06:54 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] Add knowledge base with productivity-first architecture
 and canonical transport direction

Establish the Uruquim specification, revised around three equal commitments:
performance, productivity, and AI readability.

- 01-architecture-spec: productivity as a first-class requirement, two API
  levels (Productive/Systems), five-concept public surface (app/route/
  extract/respond/serve), respond-on-failure extractors, standardized error
  envelope, non-parametric default Context with opt-in typed state, and
  core:net/http as the canonical transport behind an internal boundary
  (odin-http as bootstrap adapter only)
- 02-odin-idioms: productivity-vs-explicitness rule, AI-friendly API rules,
  compiling-example requirement (bans or_else statement blocks), sanctioned
  typeid-validated rawptr for app state
- 03-development-phases: Phase 1 recast as a productive vertical slice
  (CRUD-capable), router in Phase 2, middleware/typed state in Phase 3,
  production hardening in Phase 4, ecosystem/AI plus official core:net/http
  adapter in Phase 5
- 04-local-agent-system-prompt: adds productivity, canonical-naming, and
  transport rules for the implementation agent
- docs/: normative canonical-patterns.md, ai-context.md for coding agents,
  and phase-gated placeholders for the remaining docs

